SIMPLE: enforcement
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Enforcement
<hw>En*force"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>enforcement</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of enforcing;
compulsion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He that contendeth against these <qex>enforcements</qex> may
easily master or resist them.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Raleigh.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Confess 't was hers, and by what rough <qex>enforcement</qex>⟦br⟧
You got it from her.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A giving force to; a putting in execution.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Enforcement</qex> of strict military discipline.</q>
<rj><qau>Palfrey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which enforces, constraints, gives force,
authority, or effect to; constraint; force applied.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rewards and punishment of another life, which the Almighty has
established as the <qex>enforcements</qex> of his law.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enforcer</ent>⟦br⟧
